  "texts": [
    "In addition to these two subjects, Choi et al. (2023) also examined ChatGPT on constitutional law, federalism and separation of powers, and employee benefits.",
    "Savelka (2023) researched GPT-3.5's capabilities in relation to veterans' affairs cases, public health cases, and general commercial legal contracts.",
    "Much previous research (though we note most had not been released at the time of our study design) focused on prompt engineering in legal contexts.",
    "Yu et al. (2022) found that using the legal reasoning technique \"Issue, Rule, Application, and Conclusion\" (IRAC) in their prompts performed best.",
    "Some research (Bommarito II and Katz 2022; Savelka 2023) found that zero-shot prompting proved more effective compared to fine-tuned models, and Choi et al. (2023) determined that, generally, the simplest prompts performed best."
  ],
